  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 36.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Thou shalt cleanse the altar, when thou hast made an atonement for it",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Rather, \"thou shelf purify the altar by making an atonement for it.\" The sin-offering for the altar was the same bullock which served for Aaron and his sons. Its virtue was applied to the altar by smearing the blood upon its horns and pouring the remainder at its base (ver. 12). See ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Leviticus 8:15",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ": - \"And Moses took the blood, and put it upon the horns of the altar round about with his finger, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "and purified the altar",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and poured the blood at the bottom of the altar, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "and sanctified it",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".\" ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "And thou shalt anoint it",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". In his execution of these directions, Moses separated the anointing of the altar from the cleansing, placing it even before the anointing of Aaron. He anointed it by sprinkling the holy oil upon it seven times (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Leviticus 8:11",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). Exodus 29:36",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Keil and Delitzsch Biblical Commentary on the Old Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Consecration of Aaron and his Sons through the anointing of their persons and the offering of sacrifices, the directions for which form the subject of vv. 1-35. This can only be fully understood in connection with the sacrificial law contained in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Leviticus 1-7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". It will be more advisable therefore to defer the examination of this ceremony till we come to ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Leviticus 8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", where the consecration itself is described. The same may also be said of the expiation and anointing of the altar, which are commanded in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 29:36",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 29:37",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and carried out in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Leviticus 8:11",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  }
